@guccionmynuts I understand the frustration of people thinking that the razor ad is attacking all men.  But I saw a post the helped me understand it better,  you see ads about drunk driving yet you don’t feel personally attacked because you know it doesn’t apply to you.  The commercial is trying raise awareness about issues in men (obviously women have the same issues but the ad wasn’t about woman) and unfortunately we live in a world where some men don’t know that you respect woman, who don’t know that rape is wrong and so on.

It’s not the slogan, it’s the ad. It promotes a message that indicates that men don’t know how to control themselves. Men know how to respect women, men know that rape is wrong, and men know that misogyny is wrong. If a “man” doesn’t know any of those things, he is not a man. There are so many other issues that could have been brought to light that are so much more important, and this one is practically non-existent.
